replies.bodyText:
It's better to leave the actual send to the caller, the HttpSender might have state (e.g. user, session) which would be lost if the message is sent by the extension. The method could accept a function which sends the HttpMessage, e.g.:
public interface HttpMessageSender {
    void sendAndReceive(HttpMessage message) throws IOException;
}

